# Floating Bar Component

An extracted, standalone floating action bar component with interactive tree visualization. This component was extracted from a larger codebase and refactored to work independently without database dependencies.

## Features

- **Interactive Tree Visualization**: Uses React Flow to display hierarchical problem/task trees
- **Floating Dock Interface**: macOS-style floating action bar at the bottom of the screen
- **Collapsible Sidebar**: Full-height sidebar panel that slides in from the right
- **Status Management**: Track items through different states (not-started, in-progress, completed, blocked, approved)
- **Color-Coded Branches**: Visual distinction between different tree branches
- **Mock Data**: Fully functional with mock data - no database required
- **Responsive Design**: Works across different screen sizes

## What Was Removed

This extraction **removed all database logic** from the original implementation:
- No Drizzle ORM dependencies
- No database schema imports
- No server actions that connect to a database
- Mock functions replace all data fetching and mutations

The component now uses local mock data and simulated async operations for demonstration purposes.

## Structure

```
extracted-floating-bar/
├── src/
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── FloatingBar.tsx          # Main component
│   │   └── ui/                       # UI primitives
│   │       ├── button.tsx
│   │       ├── dialog.tsx
│   │       ├── input.tsx
│   │       ├── label.tsx
│   │       └── sheet.tsx
│   ├── lib/
│   │   ├── mock-data.ts              # Mock data and API functions
│   │   └── utils.ts                  # Utility functions
│   └── types/
│       └── index.ts                  # TypeScript types
├── package.json
└── README.md
```

## Installation

1. **Install dependencies**:
```bash
npm install
# or
yarn install
# or
pnpm install
```

2. **Set up Tailwind CSS**:

Create `tailwind.config.js`:
```js
/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
export default {
  content: [
    "./index.html",
    "./src/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}",
  ],
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        border: "hsl(var(--border))",
        input: "hsl(var(--input))",
        ring: "hsl(var(--ring))",
        background: "hsl(var(--background))",
        foreground: "hsl(var(--foreground))",
        primary: {
          DEFAULT: "hsl(var(--primary))",
          foreground: "hsl(var(--primary-foreground))",
        },
        secondary: {
          DEFAULT: "hsl(var(--secondary))",
          foreground: "hsl(var(--secondary-foreground))",
        },
        destructive: {
          DEFAULT: "hsl(var(--destructive))",
          foreground: "hsl(var(--destructive-foreground))",
        },
        muted: {
          DEFAULT: "hsl(var(--muted))",
          foreground: "hsl(var(--muted-foreground))",
        },
      },
    },
  },
  plugins: [],
}
```

3. **Add CSS variables**:

Create or update your `src/index.css`:
```css
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;

@layer base {
  :root {
    --background: 0 0% 100%;
    --foreground: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
    --muted: 210 40% 96.1%;
    --muted-foreground: 215.4 16.3% 46.9%;
    --border: 214.3 31.8% 91.4%;
    --input: 214.3 31.8% 91.4%;
    --ring: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
    --primary: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%;
    --primary-foreground: 210 40% 98%;
    --secondary: 210 40% 96.1%;
    --secondary-foreground: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%;
    --destructive: 0 84.2% 60.2%;
    --destructive-foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  }

  .dark {
    --background: 222.2 84% 4.9%;
    --foreground: 210 40% 98%;
    --muted: 217.2 32.6% 17.5%;
    --muted-foreground: 215 20.2% 65.1%;
    --border: 217.2 32.6% 17.5%;
    --input: 217.2 32.6% 17.5%;
    --ring: 212.7 26.8% 83.9%;
    --primary: 210 40% 98%;
    --primary-foreground: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%;
    --secondary: 217.2 32.6% 17.5%;
    --secondary-foreground: 210 40% 98%;
    --destructive: 0 62.8% 30.6%;
    --destructive-foreground: 210 40% 98%;
  }
}
```

## Usage

### Basic Usage

```tsx
import FloatingBar from './components/FloatingBar';

function App() {
  return (
    <div className="h-screen">
      <FloatingBar />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

### Customizing Mock Data

Edit `src/lib/mock-data.ts` to customize the project and problem data:

```typescript
export const mockProject: StartedProject = {
  id: "proj-1",
  title: "Your Project Title",
  codebaseName: "your-codebase",
};

export const mockProblems: Problem[] = [
  {
    id: "prob-1",
    projectIdeaId: "proj-1",
    parentProblemId: null, // null = root node
    title: "Your Task",
    description: "Task description",
    startedAt: null,
    completedAt: null,
    createdAt: new Date(),
  },
  // Add more problems...
];
```

### Replacing Mock Data with Real API

To integrate with a real backend, replace the functions in `src/lib/mock-data.ts`:

```typescript
// Replace mock functions with real API calls
export async function getProblemsByProject(projectId: string): Promise<Problem[]> {
  const response = await fetch(`/api/projects/${projectId}/problems`);
  return response.json();
}

export async function startProblem(id: string) {
  const response = await fetch(`/api/problems/${id}/start`, { method: 'POST' });
  return response.json();
}

// etc...
```

## Component Features

### Floating Dock
- Fixed at the bottom center of the screen
- Two action buttons: Menu and Settings
- macOS-inspired design with backdrop blur

### Sidebar Panel
- Slides in from the right
- Full height with scrollable content
- Two modes:
  - **Menu**: Shows project info, statistics, and actions
  - **Settings**: Display options and status legend

### Tree Visualization
- Automatically lays out problem/task trees using Dagre
- Color-coded by root branch
- Animated edges for in-progress items
- Click nodes to view details and take actions

### Node Interactions
- Click any node to open detail sheet
- Start not-started problems
- Mark in-progress problems as complete
- View problem metadata (depth, connections, description)

## Customization

### Status Colors
Modify `statusStyles` in `FloatingBar.tsx`:

```typescript
const statusStyles: Record<ProblemStatus, {...}> = {
  "not-started": {
    background: "#f3f4f6",
    color: "#374151",
    // ...
  },
  // Customize other statuses...
};
```

### Branch Colors
Modify `branchColors` array in `FloatingBar.tsx`:

```typescript
const branchColors = [
  "#ef4444", // red
  "#f97316", // orange
  // Add or modify colors...
];
```

### Layout Direction
Change the graph layout direction in `getLayoutedElements`:

```typescript
dagreGraph.setGraph({
  rankdir: "RL", // RL = right-to-left, LR = left-to-right, TB = top-to-bottom
  // ...
});
```

## Dependencies

### Core
- **React**: UI framework
- **@xyflow/react**: Flow diagram library for tree visualization
- **dagre**: Graph layout algorithm

### UI Components
- **@radix-ui/react-dialog**: Accessible dialog/modal
- **@radix-ui/react-label**: Accessible form labels
- **lucide-react**: Icon library

### Styling
- **Tailwind CSS**: Utility-first CSS framework
- **class-variance-authority**: Type-safe variant management
- **clsx & tailwind-merge**: Class name utilities

## Browser Support

Modern browsers with ES6+ support:
- Chrome/Edge 90+
- Firefox 88+
- Safari 14+

## License

MIT

## Credits

Extracted and adapted from a larger project management application. Database logic removed for standalone use.

